ors are required to provide new office space and other ancillary facilities. Various installations of Building Services would be implemented according to architectural layout. Interior and semioutdoor landscaping features shall be carried out at specified locations.</p>',1.00),(169,'dhd4hduxvxtuqkm6mmj5yj5o','Residential development project at 1-17 Sai Yuen Lane, Sai Ying Pun, Hong Kong','2025-06-02 06:00:42.529000','2025-07-07 07:13:53.255000','2025-07-07 07:13:53.872000',8,36,'en','Residential development project at 1-17 Sai Yuen Lane, Sai Ying Pun, Hong Kong','Grace Sky Creation Limited','01 September 2015 - 30 June 2018','<p>The scope of work consists of construction of a single residential tower of 30 storeys high, including 5 levels of podium floor, 25 storeys of residential floors, roof and upper roof. Podium portion includes 2 levels of retail shops and 2 restaurants, 1 level of plant room floor, 1 level of Club House and 1 level of sky garden. A typical floor includes studio flats, 1-bedroom and 2-bedrooms unit at total 10 flats per floor. The building envelope is cladded with pre-cast façade, curtain walling, balcony with glass balustrade, aluminum grille and panel.</p><br/><br/>',2.00),(170,'b1myzu2oryg58gon1fgn6lz6','Hong Kong International Airport Contract P562 - Project Office Fit-out Works','2025-06-02 06:04:00.080000','2025-07-07 07:13:53.407000','2025-07-07 07:13:53.898000',8,36,'en','Hong Kong International Airport Contract P562 - Project Office Fit-out Works','Airport Authority Hong Kong','21 May 2015 - 03 October 2015','<p>To support the future development of the airport, the original office area was renovated to provide sufficient facilities for personnel use.</p><p>The works consisted of demolition of the existing facilities, modification of existing raised floor, and ceiling grid system to suit the conforming design; construction of new partitions to form pantries, work stations, filing areas, and other function rooms, etc., installation of office furniture, projector system, voice and data system, and modification of MEP system, for departments and district council&#x27;s use. Seamless communications and coordination with all concerned parties was one of the major tasks of the project team.</p>',3.00),(171,'wjc0hpv8es15xda50bls7y7v','MTR Contract No. Q036895 - Maritime Square Extension Works','2025-06-02 06:07:35.712000','2025-07-07 07:13:53.434000','2025-07-07 07:13:53.941000',8,36,'en','MTR Contract No. Q036895 - Maritime Square Extension Works','MTR Corporation Ltd.','13 May 2015 - 13 November 2017','<p>The extension works&#x27; objective was to upgrade the entertainment facilities for residents to enjoy and also enhance its attractiveness as a tourist spot for visitors. It also serves as a pedestrian transport hub connecting the surrounding residential estates, MTR and public transport interchange with bridges and an all-day walkway.</p><p>The major scope of this project consisted of modification of the existing public lorry park into a 5-storey commercial complex (including a mezzanine floor). The works included the construction of superstructure works with landscape desk, implementation of Temporary Traffic Arrange (TTA) to maintain Public Transport Interchange (PTI) operation. The majority of the structural  with A&amp;A works and internal and external works would take 25 months to complete.</p>',4.00),(172,'nb040ipvcxt6veq91h8qogt9','Carcass Work Contract for Superstructure Works – Phase 7 at Planning Area 19, TCTL 5 MTRC Tung Chung Station Development – Package Three (Contract No. 511/03)','2025-06-02 06:37:35.939000','2025-07-07 07:13:53.593000','2025-07-07 07:13:53.958000',8,36,'en','Carcass Work Contract for Superstructure Works – Phase 7 at Planning Area 19, TCTL 5 MTRC Tung Chung Station Development – Package Three','Claytown Power Enterprises Limited and Cosmos Wide International Limited','13 June 2007 - 14 March 2009','<p>The approximate gross covered floor area is 19,877 m2</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Hoarding and Covered Walkways</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>56 nos. 4 storeys high Town House and 1 Storey Basement (including Pile Caps)</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Clubhouse</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>External Works</li></ul>',13.00),(173,'nhbzz1u7vogby3m6e86rmjd3','The Chinese University of Hong Kong – New Chapel to Theology Building','2025-06-02 06:30:38.183000','2025-07-07 07:13:53.443000','2025-07-07 07:13:53.983000',8,36,'en','The Chinese University of Hong Kong – New Chapel to Theology Building','The Chinese University of Hong Kong','02 October 2009 - 09 December 2011','<p>In order to provide a better environment for the student to have a devotional worship, The Chinese University of Hong Kong decided to build a new chapel.</p><p>Our group has awarded this New Chapel to Theology Building contract. The works consist of the construction of a 1,450 m2 chapel, where for accommodating 350 people. With its eastern style green glazed tiles roof, the new chapel assimilates into the natural environment. The round-shaped chapel is surrounded by windows to maximize natural light, it can save more energy and provide a nature view for the worship. The chapel also installed fourteen stained glass windows and is supported by 12 pillars with an emblem for one of the 12 disciples on each pillar.</p>',11.00),(174,'qztt4o6gbw8er0p1jh6pu96j','Construction and Fitting Out of Integrated Airport Centre (Contract M991)','2025-06-02 06:42:06.622000','2025-07-07 07:13:53.693000','2025-07-07 07:13:54.040000',8,36,'en','Construction and Fitting Out of Integrated Airport Centre','Airport Authority Hong Kong','16 November 2006 - 05 May 2007','<p>The works include the construction, fitting out and maintenance of the Integrated Airport Centre</p>',14.00),(175,'mr4d1ypgo6b3x3klgw3b1w7s','Reprovisioning of New Territories South Animal Management Centre and Shatin Plant Quarantine Station (Shatin to Central Link – Contract No. 1113)','2025-06-02 06:17:15.029000','2025-07-07 07:13:53.449000','2025-07-07 07:13:54.033000',8,36,'en','Reprovisioning of New Territories South Animal Management Centre and Shatin Plant Quarantine Station','MTR Corporation Limited','10 September 2012 - 29 November 2013','<p>The Shatin to Central Line is one of the railway lines recommended by Hong Kong Government, with a series of stations strategically built along the railway. Due to the construction of Hin Keng Station, it was neccessary to reprovision the New Territories South Animal Management Centre and Shatin Plant Quarantine Station from Tai Wai Che Kung Miu Road and Hin Keng Street to other locations.</p><p>Our group was awarded this reprovisioning project which included the reprovisioning of the three-storey New Territories South Animal Management Centre and single-storey Shatin Plant Quarantine station. With good communication and understanding with the stakeholders throughout the project, we managed toobtain consensus on the work and carried out the project smoothly.</p>',7.00),(176,'ndhrzsl9qnv9ar6lsg8qx2ns','Thrill Mountain & Polar Adventure (Ocean Park Master Redevelopment Project Contract No. CS03)','2025-06-02 06:26:39.654000','2025-07-07 07:13:53.885000','2025-07-07 07:13:54.251000',8,36,'en','Thrill Mountain & Polar Adventure','Ocean Park Corporation','02 November 2009 - 08 July 2012','<p>Ocean Park&#x27;s Master Redevelopment Plan included two new themed projects in &quot;The Summit&quot; area - &quot;Thrill Mountain&quot; and &quot;Polar Adventure&quot;, covering a total area of 400,000 square feet.</p><p>&quot;Thrill Mountain&quot; offered six attractions, booth games, as well as food, beverages and merchandise, while &quot;Polar Adventure&quot; consists of &quot;North Pole Encounter&quot;, &quot;South Pole Spectacular&quot; and &quot;Arctic Blast &quot;.</p><p>Several building materials used in the construction included fiberglass reinforced concrete for the manufacture of icebergs and imitation stones. In order to allow visitors to have the best underwater experience, the exhibition hall used transparent acrylic plates and transparent tempered glass of 202mm thickness for the construction of underwater tunnels and underwater screen. The newly opened restaurant also used transparent acrylic panel for the screen, allowing visitors to watch the Antarctic penguins while enjoying their food.</p><br/><br/>',10.00),(177,'vnfkj8oywufrkm3ojbmdldsy','Redevelopment of Disciplined Services Quarters in Fu Tei, Tuen Mun (Contract No. SS A511)','2025-06-02 06:15:47.855000','2025-07-07 07:13:54.074000','2025-07-07 07:13:55.018000',8,36,'en','Redevelopment of Disciplined Services Quarters in Fu Tei, Tuen Mun','Architectural Services Department','18 December 2012 - 14 July 2015','<p>In order to alleviate the shortage of departmental quarters for disciplined services staff, it was proposed to develop the project site in Fu Tei, Tuen Mun into a new departmental quarter.</p><p>Our group was awarded this project and the works include the construction of a 20-storey building block housing 140 quarter unit. The main building contains management office, game centre and other facilities for residents. The main building is connected to the podium floor and garden with a carpark, transformer room, generator room and other facilities. A 11m high noise-barrier was placed at the west of the building to reduce the noise level of the quarters.</p>',6.00),(178,'ddvs7kew6tkt6umf6t9gao8j',' The Management Contract for Proposed Development for Hang Seng Management College','2025-06-02 06:21:32.794000','2025-07-07 07:13:55.427000','2025-07-07 07:13:56.146000',8,36,'en','The Management Contract for Proposed Development for Hang Seng Management College','Hang Seng School of Commerce','07 October 2011 - 27 October 2015','<p>This contract is part of the development plan of Hang Seng Management College. It aims to expand a green campus which offers state-of-the-art learning, teaching, research and residential facilities to meet the needs and demands of quality tertiary education in the 21st century.</p><p>The construction comprises the proposed development at Block A, B, C, D and F for the Hang Seng Management College, which includes the S H Ho Academic Building, Sports and Amenities Centre, HSMC Plaza, Lee Quo Wei Academic Building, and HSMC Jockey Club Residential Colleges. Awarded by Hong Kong Green Building Council, the S H Ho Academic Building, Sports and Amenities Centre, Lee Quo Wei Academic Building and the student residence halls achieved Final Platinum rating in the BEAM Plus Assessment Scheme.</p>',8.00),(179,'c9f78ymo2lxnrlx46gup660f','Construction of Two 30-classroom Primary Schools at Site 1A-3 and Site 1A-4, Kai Tak Development, Kowloon (Contract No. SS B507)','2025-06-02 06:09:27.940000','2025-07-07 07:13:55.629000','2025-07-07 07:13:56.189000',8,36,'en','Construction of Two 30-classroom Primary Schools at Site 1A-3 and Site 1A-4, Kai Tak Development, Kowloon','Architectural Services Department','29 November 2013 - 31 December 2015','<p>Kai Tak Development is a huge and complicated development project spanning a total planning area of over 320 hectares. The proposal of Kai Tak Development consists of community, housing, business, tourism and infrastructural uses.</p><p>This is a community construction project which consists of the construction of two primary schools with an approximate site area of 13,200m2. The design of the school complements the concept of Kai Tak Development by including numerous environmental elements. The design also won the &quot;HKIA Merit Award of Hong Kong 2015 – Community Building&quot;. The external walls were installed with environmental wooden screens and metal screens to save the energy required by the air-conditioning system and also make the building become unique. The walls are made of Architectural concrete, creating a natural landscape and reducing the use of additional materials. In addition, gardens were set up in different locations and floors of the buildings and green roofs were set outside the library, providing students with a comfortable learning and reading environment.</p>',5.00),(180,'rlcn6rhf5mm120bvuws5d54t','九龍啟德發展計劃(地盤1A-3及地盤1A-4) 兩所設有30間課室的小學 (合約編號 SS B507)','2025-06-02 06:10:26.599000','2025-07-07 07:13:55.681000','2025-07-07 07:13:56.210000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','九龍啟德發展計劃(地盤1A-3及地盤1A-4) 兩所設有30間課室的小學','建築署','2013 年 11 月 29 日 - 2015 年 12 月 31 日','<p>啟德發展計劃是一項規模龐大和繁複的發展項目， 規劃範圍總面積逾320 公頃。啟德發展計劃的方案包含了社區、房屋、商業、旅遊和基建用途。</p><p>本合約是屬於啟德發展計劃內的社區工程項目，主要興建九龍啟德發展區兩所小學，地盤面積約為一萬三千平方米。學校設計配合啟德發展計劃的理念，加入大量環保元素。建築物設計亦獲得「香港建築師學會2015年年獎境內優異獎─社區建築」。外牆裝有環保木屏風及金屬屏風，減少日照從而降低空調系統所需的耗電量，裝飾亦使建築物外觀別具一格。牆身多處採用清水混凝土，營造出自然景觀，亦減少使用額外的飾料。此外，於建築群不同位置及樓層設置花園，圖書館外亦有綠化屋頂，為學生提供舒適的學習及閱讀的環境。</p>',5.00),(181,'tk7zrqgcp2ng0673m8uv1yjq','C&E Office, Queen\'s Warehouse and Agent\'s Offices','2025-06-02 06:59:36.913000','2025-07-07 07:13:55.672000','2025-07-07 07:13:56.220000',8,36,'en','C&E Office, Queen\'s Warehouse and Agent\'s Offices','River Trade Terminal Co. Ltd','01 March 1997 - 01 August 1998','<p>The major element of Works consisted of:</p><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of piles and foundation</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Construction of building structures</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Fuel storage tanks enclosure and LPG storage facility construction</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Design, supply and installation of roller shutters</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>E&amp;M Works for the buildings</li></ul><ul class=\"pl-6 list-disc [&amp;_ul]:list-[circle]\"><li>Fit out works</li></ul>',18.00),(182,'iaiy4dpdr4g1wot4fjzmfflh','Mei Foo Station (KCRC West Rail Project Contract No. CC-404)','2025-06-02 06:55:26.761000','2025-07-07 07:13:55.837000','2025-07-07 07:13:56.293000',8,36,'en','Mei Foo Station','Kowloon Canton Railway Corporation','02 August 1999 - 31 October 2003','<p>The Mei Foo Station is situated inside the Mei Foo Park. It adopts a fully enclosed design. The unique feature of the design is to achieve a complete integration with the Lai Chi Kok Park. The roof of the station landscaped with plants, features an innovative rooftop parkland together with play equipment and facilities for the public particularly for the densely populated adjacent estates like the Mei Foo Sun Chuen and the Ching Lai Garden. The complete integration with the surrounding environment is the main feature for both the design and construction of the station, for example: provision of sufficient footpaths and vehicular link roads between the station and the adjacent housing estates. Minimizing the impact to the adjacent residents during the construction stage was also a major concern. A temporary footbridge running across the site was constructed so as to provide convenient passage for the pedestrian. With the commencement of the operation of the West Rail and the completion and opening of the rooftop parkland at the roof of the Mei Foo station, the transportation and the environment of the surrounding area was substantially improved.The quality of living for thelocal residents was also enhanced.</p>',17.00),(183,'ekublcy6ft3mmtc40b4d896t','西營盤西源里1-17號住宅發展項目工程','2025-06-02 05:58:20.682000','2025-07-07 07:13:55.841000','2025-07-07 07:13:56.306000',8,36,'zh-Hant-HK','西營盤西源里1-17號住宅發展項目工程','天怡創建有限公司','2015 年 09 月 01 日 - 2018 年 06 月 30 日','<p>工程包括建設一座30層高的單橦住宅大樓，當中包括5層平台，25層住宅樓層，屋頂和上層屋頂。平台部分包括2層零售商店和2間餐廳，1層機房樓層，1層會所和1層空中花園。標準樓層包括開放式住宅單位，一房及兩房單位，每層合共10個單位。 建築外層結構使用預製外牆、幕牆、帶玻璃欄杆的陽台、鋁合金格柵和蓋板。</p>',2.00),(184,'ruohrcavmnb2n5xfmlecd4vr','Refurbishment of Smoking Lounges at PTB (Contract M980)','2025-06-02 06:53:56.332000','2025-07-07 07:13:56.230000','2025-07-07 07:13:56.516000',8,36,'en','Refurb